<I c="Tutorial" i="tutorial" m="tutorials.tutorial" n="tutorial_JungleAdventure_MysticalRelics" s="181695">
  <T n="category">181477<!--TutorialCategory: tutorial_category_Jungle_Adventure--></T>
  <T n="name">0x463C3736<!--String: "Mystical Relics"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae70</T>
      <T n="text">0xA61E8C9C<!--String: "Mystical Relics are powerful objects created by combining top and bottom pieces with a refined crystal. They can be used to cast powerful curses or blessings on Sims."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae73</T>
      <T n="text">0x13162096<!--String: "Top and bottom pieces of these relics are found in Omiscan Temple treasure chests and excavation sites in the Belomisia Jungle."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae72</T>
      <T n="text">0xD71FB5B0<!--String: "Each Mystical Relic is powered by a refined crystal. A Sim with Archaeology Skill can use a Archaeology Table to Refine a crystal. Crystals are either common, uncommon, or rare . These rarities influence which curse or blessing a Mystical Relic can cast."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_4.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae75</T>
      <T n="text">0xBBBB4A68<!--String: "To create a Mystical Relic a Sim needs to have all the pieces in their inventory. A top and bottom relic piece and a refined crystal are needed. First, Click on a top or bottom Mystical Relic piece and choose 'Fuse With…'. Select an appropriate piece to combine. Once completed, Click on the combined Mystical Relic piece and choose "Insert Crystal". Select the refined crystal and complete the process."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_5.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae74</T>
      <T n="text">0xB226268E<!--String: "Each Sim will have to learn through trial and error what a Mystical Relic will cast. Once a Sim has cast a mystical relic on themselves or another Sim they will learn the curse or blessing cast by that mystical relic combination. This information will be displayed in the mystical relic tooltips and in the tooltips on the pieces during the combination process."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_6.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae77</T>
      <T n="text">0xB466AFAA<!--String: "All curses can be dispelled through hard work.  Check the information on the buff for clues on how to solve the curse.  A successful solve will result in a blessing being bestowed on the Sim.\n\nSims can also dispel curses by donating to the Statue of Madre Cosecha. This will not result in a blessing."--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_7.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae76</T>
      <T n="text">0x79F8686D<!--String: "Mystical Relics need time to recharge after casting a curse or blessing. If a Sim has casted a curse recently they will have to wait a few hours for the Mystical Relic to recharge.\n\nWhen a Sim is affected by curse or a blessing on them they cannot receive another curse or blessing. "--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGP06\UI\Lessons\Mystical_Relics_8.png">2f7d0004:00000000:28413e32e327ae79</T>
      <T n="text">0xC3ED6292<!--String: "Each time a curse or blessing is cast there is a chance that a Mystical Relic can be damaged. Cracks will appear if this happens. If the Mystical Relic is damaged again it will be destroyed.\n\nKeep all mystical relic pieces you find so you can replace old Mystical Relics that have been destroyed from use."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
